_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_

**Add proper type for parsed CSV rows to fix pipeline failure.**

The `any[]` type is flagged by ESLint. Define an interface for the expected CSV row structure.


<details>
<summary>🔧 Proposed fix</summary>

```diff
+interface CSVRow {
+  Date?: string;
+  date?: string;
+  DATE?: string;
+  Amount?: string;
+  amount?: string;
+  AMOUNT?: string;
+  Category?: string;
+  category?: string;
+  CATEGORY?: string;
+  Type?: string;
+  type?: string;
+  TYPE?: string;
+  Note?: string;
+  note?: string;
+  NOTE?: string;
+}

// In handleFileUpload:
-          const rows = results.data as any[];
+          const rows = results.data as CSVRow[];
```
</details>

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against the current code and only fix it if needed.

In `@src/components/Dashboard.tsx` at line 216, Replace the use of any[] for
parsed CSV rows by declaring a specific interface (e.g., interface CsvRow { /*
fields: id?: string; name: string; ... */ }) that matches the CSV schema and use
it to type the variable (change const rows = results.data as any[] to const rows
= results.data as CsvRow[]); add the CsvRow interface near the top of the
component or in a shared types file and update any downstream uses of rows
(map/filter) to use the new typed properties (referencing rows, results.data,
and the Dashboard component) so ESLint no longer flags any[].
```

</details>

